#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introducing &DSCL;s"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter introduces you to the concept and usage of &DSCL;s or &DSC;s "
"for short."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why Package Software with RPM?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The RPM Package Manager (RPM) is a package management system that runs on "
"&MAJOROS;. RPM makes it easier for you to distribute, manage, and update "
"software that you create for Fedora or Enterprise Linux. Many software "
"vendors distribute their software via a conventional archive file (such as a "
"tarball). However, there are several advantages in packaging software into "
"RPM packages. These advantages are outlined below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "With RPM, you can:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install, reinstall, remove, upgrade and verify packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Users can use standard package management tools (for example "
"<application>Yum</application> or <application>PackageKit</application>) to "
"install, reinstall, remove, upgrade and verify your RPM packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use a database of installed packages to query and verify packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because RPM maintains a database of installed packages and their files, "
"users can easily query and verify packages on their system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use metadata to describe packages, their installation instructions, and so "
"on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each RPM package includes metadata that describes the package's components, "
"version, release, size, project URL, installation instructions, and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Package pristine software sources into source and binary packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"RPM allows you to take pristine software sources and package them into "
"source and binary packages for your users. In source packages, you have the "
"pristine sources along with any patches that were used, plus complete build "
"instructions. This design eases the maintenance of the packages as new "
"versions of your software are released."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add packages to Yum repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add your package to a <application>Yum</application> repository that "
"enables clients to easily find and deploy your software."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Digitally sign your packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using a GPG signing key, you can digitally sign your package so that users "
"are able to verify the authenticity of the package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For in-depth information on what is RPM and how to use it, refer to the "
"<ulink url=\"http://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/Fedora/18/html/"
"System_Administrators_Guide/index.html\">Fedora 18 System Administrator's "
"Guide</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "What Are &DSCL;s?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With &DSCL;s, you can build and concurrently install multiple versions of "
"the same software components on your system. &DSCL;s have no impact on the "
"system versions of the packages installed by any of the conventional RPM "
"package management utilities."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "&DSCL;s:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not overwrite system files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&DSCL;s are distributed as a set of several components, which provide their "
"full functionality without overwriting system files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Are designed to avoid conflicts with system files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&DSCL;s make use of a special file system hierarchy to avoid possible "
"conflicts between a single &DSCL; and the base system installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Require no changes to the RPM package manager"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&DSCL;s require no changes to the RPM package manager present on the host "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Need only minor changes to the spec file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To convert a conventional package to a single &DSCL;, you only need to make "
"minor changes to the package spec file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allow you to build a conventional package and a &DSCL; package with a single "
"spec file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a single spec file, you can build both the conventional package and the "
"&DSCL; package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allow you to use a spec file from one &DSCL; to build a different &DSCL;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use a single spec file from one &DSCL; to build a different &DSCL;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Uniquely name all included packages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With &DSCL;'s namespace, all packages included in the &DSCL; are uniquely "
"named."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not conflict with updated packages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&DSCL;'s namespace ensures that updating packages on your system causes no "
"conflicts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can depend on other &DSCL;s"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because one &DSCL; can depend on another, you can define multiple levels of "
"dependencies."
msgstr ""

